# AgentOS

A local-first, resource-aware framework for running modular AI agents on consumer hardware.

## Overview

AgentOS provides a minimal orchestration layer for:
- spawning and terminating task-specific agents
- executing structured workflows
- storing logs and task data locally
- enforcing simple role-based behavior via SOPs

This project is designed to be:
- lightweight
- modular
- fully self-hosted

## Status

Early development (pre-MVP)

## Goals

- deterministic agent workflows
- low resource usage
- reproducible task execution
- local data ownership

## Planned Features

- task queue (SQLite)
- agent lifecycle management (spawn/kill)
- SOP-based agent definitions
- logging and replay system
- CLI interface
- optional GPU-aware execution
- local feedback system (like/dislike)

## Usage

Not yet implemented.

